      "date": "2018-01-03 20:16:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> It should be that the some blocks of the newly created file\n > are not freed in time when we call df after deletion.\n\nDo these blocks eventually get freed if enough time passes?  It seems like this is a bug in the test, and changing the recordsize is only hiding the problem.\n\nThe test is currently calling wait_delete_completed_mds(), but it seems that it should be calling wait_delete_completed() so that it is also waiting for the OST objects to be destroyed?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
